Examples for using pwtools.batch for parameter studies (create input, run
calculations, analyze results).

A parameter study can be anything. For example, typical DFT-related tasks are
    * E(V) curve (vary V or target pressure)
    * convergence study of cutoff, k-points, ... any other code parameter
    * vary the q-grid density in phonon calculations  
    * vary lattice parameters on a grid
    * ... anything where you vary one or more parameters and do a calculation
      for each parameter set  

10local_lammps_ev
    Calculate an E(V) curve of rocksalt AlN using LAMMPS (apt-get install
    lammps) using a Tersoff interatomic potential. 

20cluster_pwscf_convergence
    Plane wave cutoff convergence study using PWscf on a cluster.

30two_hosts_extend
    Complex example showing more features: extend study (add calculations
    later), generate input for many hosts at once.
